article.linkText: Flashback to '77: Marquette rides into Elite Eight
article.story: PITTSBURGH (AP) -- Julius Page scored 22 points, including six 3-pointers, as Pittsburgh beat the 320 All Stars in an exhibition game on Wednesday. The Panthers took a 24-23 lead after Carl Krauser's free throws with 9:43 to play in the first half and never trailed again. Krauser had 16 points, while Toree Morris added 14 points for Pittsburgh, which is entering the season under new coach Jamie Dixon. John Morton and Frank Wilkins each had 17 points for the 320 All Stars, while Devonaire Deas had 15 points. The Panthers return six of the top nine players from the team that went 28-5 and reached the NCAA round of 16 for a second consecutive season. Pitt has gone 57-11 over the last two seasons.
